HEADWORD: Yager
<hw>Ya"ger</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.
<ets>j⟦aum⟧ger</ets> a hunter, from <ets>jagen</ets> to chase,
hunt.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>In the German army, one belonging to
a body of light infantry armed with rifles, resembling the
<xex>chasseur</xex> of the French army.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>jager</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

